cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper is about improving the performance of neural machine translation (NMT) for low-resource languages. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which includes papers on natural language processing and machine translation. The paper also discusses transfer learning, which is a common technique in machine learning, so cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely category. Additionally, the paper uses neural networks, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions ensembling, which is a technique commonly used in computer vision, so cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is a possible category. Finally, the paper discusses improving the state-of-the-art on low-resource machine translation, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
